<DocLayout title="Contact" description="Get in touch with the AEGIS Initiative — general inquiries, press, and policy engagement.">
  <h1>Contact</h1>

  <p>
    The AEGIS Initiative welcomes inquiries from policymakers, researchers,
    journalists, and anyone interested in governance-first AI security.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>General Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For general inquiries about the AEGIS Initiative, its publications, or
      its governance framework:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@aegis-initiative.com">contact@aegis-initiative.com</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Press Inquiries</h2>
    <p>
      For press inquiries, interview requests, or media access to brand assets
      and press-ready materials:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:press@aegis-initiative.com">press@aegis-initiative.com</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      See the <a href="/press/">Press</a> section for published articles, press
      releases, and the media kit.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Policy Engagement</h2>
    <p>
      For collaboration on policy research, standards body engagement, or
      academic partnerships:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:policy@aegis-initiative.com">policy@aegis-initiative.com</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      AEGIS engages with standards bodies (NIST, IEEE), regulatory agencies,
      legislative offices, and academic institutions. We welcome invitations to
      submit public comments, provide testimony, or collaborate on governance
      research.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>GitHub</h2>
    <p>
      All AEGIS specifications and source code are maintained on GitHub under
      the <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative">aegis-initiative</a>
      organization. Issues and discussions are welcome on any public repository.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocLayout>
